1️⃣ Present Tense
1. Simple Present

Structure: Subject + V1
Example:

I play cricket.

She reads a book.

2. Present Continuous

Structure: Subject + am/is/are + V1 + ing
Example:

I am playing cricket.

She is reading a book.

3. Present Perfect

Structure: Subject + has/have + V3
Example:

I have finished my work.

She has eaten food.

4. Present Perfect Continuous

Structure: Subject + has/have + been + V1 + ing
Example:

I have been studying for two hours.

She has been working since morning.

2️⃣ Past Tense
5. Simple Past

Structure: Subject + V2
Example:

I played cricket yesterday.

She read a book last night.

6. Past Continuous

Structure: Subject + was/were + V1 + ing
Example:

I was playing cricket.

They were watching TV.

7. Past Perfect

Structure: Subject + had + V3
Example:

I had finished my work.

She had left the office.

8. Past Perfect Continuous

Structure: Subject + had been + V1 + ing
Example:

I had been studying for two hours.

They had been waiting for a long time.

3️⃣ Future Tense
9. Simple Future

Structure: Subject + will + V1
Example:

I will play cricket tomorrow.

She will go to school.

10. Future Continuous

Structure: Subject + will be + V1 + ing
Example:

I will be studying tomorrow.

They will be playing cricket.

11. Future Perfect

Structure: Subject + will have + V3
Example:

I will have finished my work.

She will have arrived.

12. Future Perfect Continuous

Structure: Subject + will have been + V1 + ing
Example:

I will have been studying for two hours.

They will have been working all day.

✅ Simple Trick to Remember

Present → now

Past → already happened

Future → will happen later
